definition.value: A pyrimidone that is uracil which is substituted at positions 1, 5, and 6 by ethoxymethyl, isopropyl, and 3,5-dimethylbenzyl groups, respectively.
A D-glucopyranuronic acid in which the anomeric centre has alpha-configuration.
A monocarboxylic acid amide formed between benzylpenicillin and benzylamine.
A 1-phenylpropan-2-amine that has R configuration.
An imidazoquinoline that is 3H-imidazo[4,5-f]quinoline substituted by a methyl group at position 3 and an amino group at position 2.
The open chain form of D-glucose.
An aminoglycoside antibiotic produced by Micromonospora rhodorangea. It blocks polypeptide synthesis  by inhibiting the elongation step in both prokaryotic and eukaryotic cells.
A monosaccharide derivative that is the 6-O-(2R,3R,23Z,33Z)-3-hydroxy-2-octyldopentaconta-23,33-dienoyl derivative of alpha-L-idopyranose
The (R)-enantiomer of gabaculine.
A gamma-amino acid that is cyclohexane substituted at position 1 by aminomethyl and carboxymethyl groups. Used for treatment of neuropathic pain and restless legs syndrome.
A N-sulfo-D-glucosamine with an alpha-configuration at the anomeric position.
The (2R,4S)-diastereomer of 2,4-diaminopentanoic acid
A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by removal of a proton from both of the carboxylic acid groups of 5-dehydro-4-deoxy-D-glucarate.
An aminocarboxamidine, the parent compound of the guanidines.
Puromycin derivative that lacks the methoxyphenylalanyl group on the amine of the sugar ring.

A deoxygluconolactone that results from the cyclisation and formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-amino-2-deoxy-D-gluconic acid with its 5-hydroxy group. It is a sex pheromone found in the urine of female blue crabs, Callinectes sapidus.
A dicarboxylic acid monoamide of glutaric acid containing benzene and piperidinium moieties; a transition state analogue hapten used to elicit catalytic antibodies 5C8 and 14B9.
A thiosugar that is beta-D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 1 is replaced by a sulfanyl group
A L-galactopyranose with an alpha-configuration at the anomeric center.
A carbohydrate acid derivative anion that is HP_dp02_0008 [alpha-Delta4,5-UA(2S)-(1->4)-alpha-D-GlcpNS] in which the carboxy, sulfamic acid, and sulfooxy groups have undergone deprotonation.
An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the amino group of cyclohexylamine.
A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative consisting of L-proline ortho- and peri-fused on to (3S)-3-amino-1,3,4,5-tetrahydro-2H-1-benzazepin-2-one.
